# Rule 000 - Bootstrap Guard

Before doing ANY task, read [.planning/.bootstrap.json](mdc:.planning/.bootstrap.json).

If `bootstrapped === false`:

1. STOP all work.
2. Do NOT create a `.cursorrules` of your own.
3. Do NOT scaffold any code, config, or framework.
4. Instruct the user to run:
   - `npm create cursor-claude-hybrid@latest .` (inside this directory, with `--force` if needed)
   - OR `npm run bootstrap` if the template is already cloned.
5. Re-read `.planning/.bootstrap.json` after the user confirms the command ran.

If `bootstrapped === true`, proceed to Rule 005 (venture gate) before any other action.

## Rationale

This project uses the Cursor + Claude Code hybrid template. The template has self-enforcing rules, security hooks, and a mandatory Company-of-One discovery gate. Bypassing the bootstrap leaves the project without those guardrails and silently reintroduces the problems the template was designed to prevent.

